
README

   This distribution contains a SAML demo application written in Java.  It
   demonstrates an identity provider which authenticates users using the Google
   Apps Single Sign-On service.

   See this article at the Google Code website for an introduction to the Google
   Apps Single Sign-On service:

      http://code.google.com/apis/apps/sso/saml_reference_implementation.html


REQUIREMENTS

   This application has been tested using the following software.  You may need
   to install these libraries or packages to run the demo.

    *   Java 5 or later.
    *   Apache Ant 1.6 or later.
    *   Java Servlet API 2.4 or later.
    *   Apache Tomcat 5.5 or later (or equivalent).


INSTALL

   1.  Edit build.properties.
   2.  Build the application with ant: ant war
   3.  Deploy the resulting .war file to a Servlet container.

   Read this article which describes how use the demo:

      http://code.google.com/apis/apps/sso/saml_reference_implementation_web.html


SUPPORT

   Google does not offer any support for this sample code. You can find answers
   by asking the Google Apps APIs discussion group at:

      http://groups.google.com/group/google-apps-apis


